cs.GT, cs.SI, cs.CE, cs.IT, cs.MA 

The paper uses game theoretic analysis to model competition between middlemen in a two-sided platform, which falls under the category of algorithmic game theory (cs.GT). The paper also discusses decision-making under ambiguity, which is a topic in both social and information sciences (cs.SI). The concept of a two-sided platform also relates to computational economics (cs.CE). The paper also uses techniques from information theory (cs.IT) and mathematical analysis (cs.MA) to model and analyze the competition.
